  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Peel and finely dice the<strong> brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sausage-casserole-with-mash-and-green-beans/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>Cumberland sausages</strong> and cook for 2 min on each side or until browned all over</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sausage-casserole-with-mash-and-green-beans/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped carrot</strong> and <strong>onion</strong> to the pan with the sausages with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p>\n<p>Reduce the heat to medium and cook for 6-8 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sausage-casserole-with-mash-and-green-beans/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Peel the<strong> potatoes</strong> and cut them into large bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of boiling water with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 15-20 min or until fork-tender</p>\n<p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sausage-casserole-with-mash-and-green-beans/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion and carrot have softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong> and <strong>dried oregano</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 sec</p>\n<p>Crumble in the <strong>chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>add the<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> and 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Give everything a good mix up and cook for 10-15 min or until the sauce has thickened and the sausages are cooked through</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sausage-casserole-with-mash-and-green-beans/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, re-boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>green beans</strong> to a pot, cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> until fully submerged and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once boiling, cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a bite</p>\n<p>Once done, drain and return to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sausage-casserole-with-mash-and-green-beans/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the<strong> drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat and add a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a large knob of <strong>butter</strong></p>\n<p>Mash until smooth, then season generously with <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/classic-sausage-casserole-with-mash-and-green-beans/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sausage casserole</strong> over the <strong>mash</strong> with the <strong>green beans</strong> to the side</p>\n<p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
